            <scopecontent id="aspace_e374ca18b01e1b129910a5778991bf0f">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I contains 165 letters to or from Isaac Dewey Harmon. Letters concern both family and business matters primarily in Chicago, Naperville, and Peru, Illinois. Among the correspondents are brother Charles Loommis Harmon, father E. D. Harmon, mother Welthyan Loomis Harmon, sisters Harriet Harmon and Welthyan Loomis Harmon, and business partner Charles Coffing.</p>
            </scopecontent>
