               <scopecontent id="aspace_e33d8a0d4bb94fb6fd35e82ce8a47ba3">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>21 autograph letters, signed, from Churchill Coffing to Isaac Dewey Harmon concerning a business partnership between Coffing, Dewey, and E. D. Taylor. From Salisbury, Connecticut, Coffing writes of his finances and bank debts; requests updates on the construction of a warehouse in Peru, Illinois; and requests the dissolution of the partnership in 1850. Multiple letters mention cholera in New York in addition to economic conditions.</p>
                  <p>Accompanied by partial typed transcripts made by dealer.</p>
               </scopecontent>
