                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>30 autograph letters, signed, from Charles L. Harmon to Isaac Dewey Harmon concerning business matters relating to their partnership with H. G. Loomis (Harmon, Loomis &amp; Co.). Charles writes from New York, New York; Philadelphia, Pennsylvania; Detroit, Michigan; Naperville, Illinois; Saint Louis, Missouri; and Chicago, Illinois, noting the purchase of fabrics and other dry goods, attempts to secure investors and funding, and his hopes for the partnership. He also comments on economic and political conditions.</p>
                  <p>Accompanied by partial typed transcripts made by dealer.</p>
               </scopecontent>
