               <scopecontent id="aspace_97ff6a090ec002b5368440767168aa4b">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>11 autograph letters, signed, from Isaac Dewey Harmon to Charles L. Harmon detaling the economic and social conditions of Chicago, Illinois. Isaac writes of the health of the Harmon family, of his own economic prospects, and of his desire to open a store with Charles. He also requests from Charles information about Burlington, Vermont.</p>
                  <p>An autograph agreement, signed, between Isaac and Elijah Dewey Harmon absolves Isaac of his financial obligations to his father; a manuscript copy of another agreement authorizes Charles Harmon to make decisions on Isaac's behalf while in a partnership between himself, Isaac, and H. G. Loomis.</p>
                  <p>Accompanied by partial typed transcripts made by dealer.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
