               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_a24ac644522620668895a6c9fae231db">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>28 autograph letters, signed, between Isaac Dewey Harmon and Dr. Elijah Dewey Harmon and Welthyan Loomis Harmon concerning Isaac and his parents' health, the state of Harmon &amp; Loomis Co., and the parties' respective travels. Isaac writes of having purchased land in Texas, of his experiences at Niagara Falls and Philadelphia, and of his struggles with leprosy. Welthyan writes of her impending move from Burlington, Vermont, to Chicago, Illinois; Elijah writes of his move from Naperville, Illinois, to Bastrop, Texas, and the possibility of growing crops for the Chicago market.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
