                  <p>31 autograph letters, signed, from Solon Gee, Giles Spring, C. C. Smith, Charles Bingley Hosmer, Edwin R. Harmon, Hyrum Pearsons, Grant Goodrich, George A. O. Beaumont, Henry C. Meyers, I. Mark Smith, Mark Skinner, Henry Loomis Pearle, Thomas Hoyne, I. B. Lorett, John Day, Samuel Lisle Smith, and William H. Clark to Isaac Dewey Harmon. Letters concern politics, economics, and personal health; included are letters of introduction on Harmon's behalf. Most letters have been sent from either Chicago, Illinois, or Washington, D.C.</p>
