               <scopecontent id="aspace_cced9f7ffab66f43e37a3c7fe469d886">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Autograph manuscript journal (circa 420 pages, partically blank), signed, kept by Isaac Dewey Harmon during his travels through the Republic of Texas from 1839 November 21 to 1840 March 1. Journal includes descriptions of Galveston, Houston, and Austin, Texas, as well as New Orleans, Louisiana, and the Mississippi River. Later entries document Harmon's time in Chicago, Illinois, from 1840 March 1 to 1859 October.</p>
                  <p>Accompanied by a partial typed transcript made by dealer.</p>
               </scopecontent>
